[h1]Vigil at the Holy Site[/h1]

Devote yourself to your faith, and offer up a captive to seal the rite.

[h2]The Vigil[/h2]
A once-per-game player decision. Sacrifice a captive at the holy place; receive 5,000 piety. The flavor text adapts to your faith family: Norse, Christian, Islamic, Tengri, or generic.

[h2]Burn the Infidel Holy Place[/h2]
After the Vigil, a second decision unlocks. While your army stands on a holy site of another faith that you hold by right, by siege, or have just raided, you may burn and desecrate it. The act grants another 5,000 piety and leaves the county under a Desecrated Ground modifier for 80 years (-100% tax, -50% levy).

[h2]Consequences[/h2]
The faith of the desecrated holy place takes notice. From the pool of root's vassals-or-below and neighboring top-liege rulers of that faith:

[list]
[*] The most cunning believer (highest intrigue) becomes your rival and starts a murder scheme against you.
[*] The strongest landed believer (highest max military strength) becomes your rival and declares a Punitive War. The wargoal is your captivity: on their victory, you are dragged in chains to their dungeon. If the holy place lay inside your own realm, the war also strips its de jure duchy from you on defeat.
[*] If the same character is both, they take both roles.
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
[b]CK3 1.19.[/b] Adds new content (one tradition file path is untouched; this mod adds decisions, a casus belli, modifiers, and loc). Does not edit vanilla files.
